1
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:21,896
KANTO
MATSUBARA-GUMI

2
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:24,065
- Hello there.
- Hi. How's business?

3
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:26,109
- Very good.
- Looks like things are going well here.

4
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,652
Oh, yes.

5
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:30,989
<i>Wherever there's money,</i>
<i>there is always the yakuza.</i>

6
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:32,240
Keep it up.

7
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:33,575
<i>That's how it's always been.</i>

8
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,787
<i>The weak ones get stripped</i>
<i>of everything they have.</i>

9
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:43,418
<i>And ever since I was young,</i>
<i>I swore I would never live like that.</i>

10
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:57,951
A MAJOR SHOCHIKU FILM
THE BALL AT THE ANJO HOUSE

11
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:13,091
270 DAYS UNTIL
THE TOKYO OLYMPIC GAMES

12
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,819
- Thank you.
- Here you are.

13
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:34,988
- You can keep the change.
- Thanks.

14
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:37,699
All right.

15
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:40,785
Come take a look!

16
00:02:44,622 --> 00:02:47,167
A very happy New Year to you, dear Kazuko.

17
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:51,212
And a very happy New Year to you as well.

18
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:08,479
It looks like there's 50,000 extra here.

19
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,356
That's the interest.

20
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:14,068
Oh, but that really won't be necessary.
After all, it's only been a week.

21
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:15,153
Please.

22
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:19,199
I don't want you to think
that I'm some kind of conman.

23
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:22,285
Good evening. Forgive the intrusion.

24
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:24,454
Please, won't you accept it?

25
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,415
All right. Thank you.

26
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:36,174
I was wondering if there was anything else
I might be able to do for you?

27
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:39,135
Just stop in here
to see us every now and again.

28
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,553
Oh, no.

29
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,847
That's not nearly good enough for you.

30
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,225
You know, that money…

31
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:47,101
Well, that money saved me.

32
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,144
Ah.

33
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:51,064
Ask me for anything.
Please, don't be shy about it.

34
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:53,524
Why not ask him to help you find a house?

35
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,610
- That's Sudo-san's profession.
- Oh.

36
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:56,819
You want a house?

37
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,906
The apartment I'm living in now
is getting a bit cramped.

38
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:04,160
Is that so? You know,
I've got the perfect property for you.

39
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:45,493
Come in.

40
00:04:48,871 --> 00:04:49,747
Hello there.

41
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:50,665
Hi.

42
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:53,584
I've been waiting for you.

43
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:57,755
Is something the matter?

44
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:58,923
Uh, no.

45
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:02,593
It's just that I've never seen you
during the day.

46
00:05:04,012 --> 00:05:05,305
Ah.

47
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:06,681
Oh, right. I'm sorry.

48
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:09,767
I didn't have time to put on much makeup.
I was in such a rush to leave.

49
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:12,020
Oh, no.
I actually prefer how you look now.

50
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,485
Uh, sorry. That was rude.

51
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:23,156
Okay. Let's get going.
I'll show you the property.

52
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,115
All right.

53
00:05:27,201 --> 00:05:29,579
It's not easy
to find a property that suits her.

54
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:32,999
Actually, she's the owner
of three clubs in Ginza.

55
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:36,377
Wow. That's impressive,
especially for someone so young.

56
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:38,212
Yeah, she really is.

57
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,423
Well, it's a beautiful house,

58
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,592
and it'll be even more beautiful
with you in it.

59
00:05:43,968 --> 00:05:45,386
Uh, earlier,

60
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:48,473
he told me that what was missing here
was a beautiful woman's touch.

61
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:49,891
I hope you're not offended.

62
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:50,975
Ah.

63
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,561
- Well, I'm off, then.
- Hmm.

64
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,646
So, please, take your time.

65
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:57,690
Thank you.

66
00:05:57,774 --> 00:05:58,733
Thank you.

67
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,778
He's a well-known American diplomat.

68
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:02,695
Ah.

69
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:05,198
He's selling the house
because he's returning to the US.

70
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:06,407
Hmm.

71
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,909
Shall we go inside and take a look?

72
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,330
What a gorgeous estate.

73
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:15,541
I think this house
will suit you very well.

74
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:16,501
Hmm.

75
00:06:23,007 --> 00:06:25,093
Will you be living here with your family?

76
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:27,178
Oh.

77
00:06:27,261 --> 00:06:29,597
Well, I just got a divorce last year,

78
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,724
so, for the moment, it's just me now.

79
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:32,683
Ah.

80
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,528
It would be wonderful
to live in a house like this,

81
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:48,116
but it might be
a little too big for just one person.

82
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:51,953
Surely, you'll meet
someone wonderful soon.

83
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:56,207
I certainly hope so.

84
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:37,748
I already told you this was the last time!

85
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,668
Don't say I didn't warn you!
You better be ready for me!

86
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,145
I'm also

87
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:04,025
involved with some illegal business deals

88
00:08:05,526 --> 00:08:09,238
aside from
the regular real estate transactions.

89
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:15,036
I cheat people and threaten them.

90
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,540
Then I acquire their property by force

91
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,376
and profit by reselling it.

92
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,591
I was

93
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:31,552
a war orphan.

94
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:36,974
I survived the post-war chaos
as best as I could,

95
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:39,519
which meant committing crimes.

96
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:44,774
And that's what I've become.

97
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:46,317
A two-bit criminal.

98
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,987
You could never trust a person like me,
could you?

99
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,624
Thank you for being so honest with me.

100
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:06,712
I was similar to you.

101
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:12,468
I was desperate to survive after the war.

102
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,845
I also did some very shameful things.

103
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:22,395
Except, now, you're
an extremely successful entrepreneur

104
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,397
with three clubs in Ginza.

105
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,774
I'm no entrepreneur.

106
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:29,569
Me neither.

107
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:33,072
But I wanna leave
this dirty business behind.

108
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:37,535
One day, I wanna make my dream come true.

109
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,252
I'm very sorry, ma'am.

110
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,505
I made you come all this way for nothing.

111
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:53,050
Why don't we pretend
that none of this ever happened?

112
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:58,598
I'll buy it. I want the house.

113
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:03,894
In that case, I'll have
a legitimate company broker the sale.

114
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:04,937
Stop.

115
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,106
I wanna buy it from you.

116
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:18,826
Thank you very much.

117
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:24,707
Hey.

118
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:28,252
How about going on a date with me?

119
00:10:56,781 --> 00:10:58,032
Ah!

120
00:10:58,115 --> 00:10:59,867
This is beautiful.

121
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,039
Thank you.

122
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:17,551
So, what is your dream?

123
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:22,390
Earlier, you said that you had a dream
that you wanted to make come true.

124
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:23,474
Well,

125
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,811
I wanna open a world-class nightclub.

126
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:31,023
One that serves top-tier food
and puts on top-tier shows.

127
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:35,569
Something… that's even better
than the Latin Quarter Club.

128
00:11:35,653 --> 00:11:37,655
That's not what I expected from you.

129
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:39,699
When I was a kid,

130
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:42,910
I often couldn't sleep
because I was so hungry.

131
00:11:42,993 --> 00:11:45,037
That would happen to me too.

132
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,501
On nights like that,
I would always imagine

133
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:53,671
watching gorgeous women

134
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:57,341
dancing onstage in beautiful costumes.

135
00:11:58,509 --> 00:12:01,470
And I would be eating
the most delicious food.

136
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:04,140
That would usually help
take my mind off the hunger.

137
00:12:05,141 --> 00:12:07,768
My dream was
that I would become an actress.

138
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:12,940
I would imagine myself
wearing a beautiful dress

139
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:16,235
and dancing with a handsome man,
like in American movies.

140
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:28,664
May I please have this dance, miss?

141
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,379
I'm sorry.

142
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:19,089
I got a bit carried away.

143
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:28,516
You know, I'm… still not a man
that's worthy of your company.

144
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:33,521
But if… you can be patient,

145
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,273
then I'll definitely

146
00:13:36,857 --> 00:13:40,152
sever all ties with my illicit business.

147
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:43,489
And, uh,

148
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:46,909
when that day finally comes…

149
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,414
I understand.

150
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:57,419
I'll wait for you.

151
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,257
- You got it?
- Yeah.

152
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:04,593
- Ah, thank you so much.
- We're fine here. We're good.

153
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:05,761
It's all right.

154
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:07,096
Here we are.

155
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,265
Oh, no, ma'am. We'll take care of that.

156
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:10,891
I can handle this much, thanks.

157
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,685
Thank you, thank you. We appreciate it.

158
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:16,397
Oh, will you please
put that against the wall?

159
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,319
Uh, you can put that chair
in the room at the back.

160
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,363
- All right, thank you.
- Thank you.

161
00:14:24,446 --> 00:14:26,156
- Will you be all right?
- Miss Kazuko.

162
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,074
Yes?

163
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:29,660
Uh, Nakazono-san
sent these in congratulations.

164
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:32,621
Oh my goodness. He really shouldn't have.

165
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,582
- Careful now.
- Thank you.

166
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:40,296
Who is this Nakazono-san?

167
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:43,716
He's my benefactor.
My investor and my business partner.

168
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:44,967
Your business partner?

169
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,886
Yes, in name only.

170
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:50,639
He's got connections in many industries,
and I consult with him from time to time.

171
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,557
Hmm.

172
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:54,643
- Is this all right here, ma'am?
- Ah, I'll be right with you.

173
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:00,441
<i>1964.</i>

174
00:15:02,651 --> 00:15:06,238
<i>If someone were to ask me</i>
<i>what the best year of my life was,</i>

175
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:10,284
<i>I'd probably say it was 1964.</i>

176
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,079
<i>It was such a good year.</i>

177
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:22,296
<i>I'd found myself a beautiful house,</i>
<i>and my clubs were all doing well.</i>

178
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:26,884
<i>Tokyo was full of energy and life,</i>

179
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:28,594
<i>and I was still so young.</i>

180
00:15:30,512 --> 00:15:33,057
<i>My dreams were growing bigger and bigger,</i>

181
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:37,019
<i>and I truly believed that tomorrow</i>
<i>would be better than today.</i>

182
00:15:37,853 --> 00:15:40,522
<i>I believed it</i>
<i>with all my heart in those days.</i>

183
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:56,664
Oh, what? Oh.

184
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,123
- Mm.
- You sure this is safe?

185
00:15:58,207 --> 00:15:59,291
Yes, you're safe.

186
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,294
Are you sure this is… Ah!

187
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:03,796
Oh! What is this?

188
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,172
You're fine. You're safe, really.

189
00:16:05,255 --> 00:16:06,799
Two.

190
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:08,842
Three…

191
00:16:09,593 --> 00:16:10,844
Okay, now turn left here.

192
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:12,304
- Left?
- Yeah.

193
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,181
Straight ahead.

194
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:16,642
- All right.
- Slowly.

195
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,727
It's all right.

196
00:16:20,562 --> 00:16:22,314
- I've got you.
- Are we almost there?

197
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,315
Yeah.

198
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:24,233
Okay.

199
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:25,609
We're here.

200
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:30,864
Huh?

201
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:35,327
What is this place?

202
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:39,081
I finally cut ties
with my illegal business.

203
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:40,499
What?

204
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:44,169
This… is a place
where dreams can come true.

205
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:47,256
How about a nightclub?

206
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:52,678
Ginza's not the hot spot
for nightclubs anymore.

207
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:54,763
Now the best place is Akasaka.

208
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:58,350
But this place is so huge.
It must cost a fortune.

209
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:01,145
If you add the start-up
and operating costs,

210
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:02,479
it's 200 million.

211
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:04,064
200 million, huh?

212
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:05,816
I have prospects for 100,

213
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:09,570
but I still need the rest,
so I'll definitely figure something out.

214
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:13,032
If this place gets off the ground, then I…

215
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:17,077
Huh? What?

216
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:18,912
No. I should stop for now.

217
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:22,249
- What? Just say it already.
- I'll tell you someday, but not yet.

218
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:24,209
Oh, come on.

219
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:25,711
You're way too proper.

220
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:33,135
Will you be
my business partner for this place?

221
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:34,970
Huh?

222
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:38,849
Well, I've never dealt with customers.

223
00:17:40,476 --> 00:17:42,686
I could really use your help.

224
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:53,655
Well, if you put it that way, I accept.

225
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:55,908
Really?

226
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:58,952
So I'll put up the remaining 100 million.

227
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:00,287
No, no.

228
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:03,832
No, no, no, no.
I can't let you take on that risk.

229
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,293
Putting up the deeds
to the clubs and the house as collateral,

230
00:18:06,376 --> 00:18:08,253
I can manage 100 million.

231
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:12,674
So you're really

232
00:18:13,717 --> 00:18:14,843
okay with that?

233
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:18,764
I'm your business partner. Of course I am.

234
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,687
Thank you so much.

235
00:18:30,025 --> 00:18:32,277
We could have the stage over there

236
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:34,905
and a bar counter over here.

237
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:38,408
That way, there would be
plenty of space between tables,

238
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:40,119
which would be spread out around here.

239
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:41,036
Oh!

240
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:42,746
Something else.

241
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:45,916
If we're gonna have shows,
we'll need a big backstage area.

242
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:46,834
Hey.

243
00:18:47,376 --> 00:18:48,210
Hmm?

244
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:51,672
What kind of person is Nakazono-san?

245
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:55,050
Oh, I already told you.
Don't you remember?

246
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:57,052
He's my investor
and also my business partner.

247
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,763
No, that isn't what I meant. Um…

248
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:02,349
Are the two of you romantically involved?

249
00:19:05,894 --> 00:19:09,231
Certainly not! No, don't be silly.

250
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:10,149
Oh.

251
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,359
Why? Are you jealous of him?

252
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:13,318
No.

253
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:16,780
I have to tell you,

254
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:20,617
I don't want you seeing him anymore.

255
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:23,620
Ah.

256
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:29,668
I just…

257
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,714
want it to be the two of us.

258
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:37,843
Oh.

259
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:39,970
Mm.

260
00:19:41,096 --> 00:19:42,431
I understand.

261
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:44,433
If you want that, then I'll do it.

262
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:01,700
Hello.

263
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:13,295
I'll be operating on my own from now on.

264
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,340
Thank you so much

265
00:20:17,507 --> 00:20:19,509
for all your support over the years.

266
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,597
I've made a huge amount of money
thanks to you.

267
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,767
I should be thanking you instead.

268
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:33,315
Hisao told me the news…

269
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:37,444
that you have a boyfriend now.

270
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:39,655
Is this because of him?

271
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,703
Yutaka Sudo.

272
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:51,208
I'm sorry to be nosy,
but I did have to look into him.

273
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:56,838
He's been running a very shady business.

274
00:20:57,547 --> 00:20:59,883
He isn't involved
in that business anymore.

275
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:02,678
He already told me everything
about his past.

276
00:21:03,553 --> 00:21:05,138
He is a sincere person.

277
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,016
This is going to sound harsh.

278
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:10,560
You should break up
with that man immediately.

279
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:19,069
Kazuko, listen.

280
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:24,908
You don't know anything about him.

281
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:31,498
Our paths will never cross again.

282
00:21:31,581 --> 00:21:34,126
Kazuko, wait! Listen to me!

283
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:42,759
FINANCIAL CONSUMER LOAN AGREEMENT
KAZUKO HOSOKI

284
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:44,886
AMOUNT: 100 MILLION YEN
DUE: APRIL 25, 1968

285
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:55,731
Here.

286
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:05,824
- This now completes the loan process.
- Thank you.

287
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:08,493
Now, if you'll be kind enough
to verify the money.

288
00:22:50,994 --> 00:22:52,329
I'm going home.

289
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:53,955
Okay, have a good night.

290
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:56,416
Don't push yourself too hard, now.

291
00:22:57,959 --> 00:22:58,877
Good work today.

292
00:23:30,283 --> 00:23:34,037
I want to be very intentional
about the entrance and the stairs.

293
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:37,082
We need something that makes
the customers feel rich and spoiled

294
00:23:37,165 --> 00:23:38,834
even before they get to their tables.

295
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:41,586
It needs to feel like
it's also part of the floor show.

296
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:44,423
I want the front area to represent
what this nightclub is all about.

297
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:45,715
- Yes, I understand.
- You do?

298
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:48,969
- Kazuko-san.
- Mm? Oh, thank you.

299
00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:51,471
This is a little something that I drew.

300
00:23:51,555 --> 00:23:52,389
Oh.

301
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:55,016
I really want the stairs
to look exactly like it.

302
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,394
Please, make it look like this,
no matter how much it costs.

303
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:59,271
Ah. Very good.

304
00:24:00,147 --> 00:24:01,481
Right, let's do it.

305
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:04,025
Thank you so very much!

306
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:31,261
Oh, it's beautiful.

307
00:24:31,344 --> 00:24:32,762
- Yeah, I like it.
- You think?

308
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:33,847
It's a good place.

309
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:35,265
- Hi.
- Oh, hi.

310
00:24:35,348 --> 00:24:37,350
- Thank you for coming.
- Oh, this is an amazing place.

311
00:24:37,434 --> 00:24:39,936
Ah, hello there.
Nice to meet you. Welcome.

312
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:42,939
- Please.
- Hi. Thank you very much.

313
00:24:43,023 --> 00:24:45,358
- Let me show you to your seats.
- Thanks.

314
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:46,359
Thank you.

315
00:24:46,985 --> 00:24:48,528
Whoa, we're packed tonight.

316
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:03,812
Good evening.
Hope you're enjoying yourselves.

317
00:26:04,604 --> 00:26:07,649
Now we have a few words
from the owners of this club,

318
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:10,443
Kazuko Hosoki and Sudo Yutaka.

319
00:26:10,527 --> 00:26:13,280
Ladies and gentlemen,
please give them a warm welcome.

320
00:26:34,801 --> 00:26:39,014
<i>Look at me</i>

321
00:26:39,556 --> 00:26:45,937
<i>I'm as helpless as a kitten up a tree</i>

322
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:51,026
<i>And I feel like</i>
<i>I'm clingin' to a cloud</i>

323
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:55,030
<i>I can't understand</i>

324
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,407
<i>I get misty…</i>

325
00:26:57,490 --> 00:27:01,202
Wow. She looks like a movie star.

326
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:05,081
Ah!

327
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:09,044
<i>Walk my way</i>

328
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:16,301
<i>And a thousand violins begin to play</i>

329
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:22,265
<i>Or it might be the sound of your hello</i>

330
00:27:22,349 --> 00:27:25,810
<i>That music I hear</i>

331
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:28,438
<i>I get misty</i>

332
00:27:34,277 --> 00:27:35,695
Ladies and gentlemen,

333
00:27:36,196 --> 00:27:38,657
we're honored to have you here with us

334
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:40,909
at Enka Nightclub this evening.

335
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:43,745
We sincerely thank you all very much.

336
00:27:45,205 --> 00:27:48,792
This nightclub is a dream shared

337
00:27:49,292 --> 00:27:51,252
by Sudo and myself.

338
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:55,465
And now that it's finally open,

339
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:57,175
well, I…

340
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:01,012
I still feel like I'm in a dream.

341
00:28:03,473 --> 00:28:05,308
We love you!

342
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,820
We will do our very best

343
00:28:17,570 --> 00:28:21,032
to ensure that your experience
is like a dream come true,

344
00:28:21,116 --> 00:28:25,120
with fine dining
and entertainment and luxury.

345
00:28:25,203 --> 00:28:29,249
So we ask you very humbly
for your continued support.

346
00:28:29,332 --> 00:28:31,209
We're so grateful to have you here.

347
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:36,047
Bravo!

348
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:56,359
DAUGHTERS' KITCHEN

349
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,293
It seems like her business is thriving.

350
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:17,422
I hope that all my concerns
are just groundless fears.

351
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:22,677
Kazuko and I have been drifting
further and further apart

352
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:25,138
from one another for so long now.

353
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:29,809
Poor Mom has been saying that
quite a lot lately, you know?

354
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:32,937
To be honest with you, Nakazono-san,

355
00:29:33,688 --> 00:29:37,942
I've been going to a fortune teller
to have him read Kazuko's fortune.

356
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:40,987
He said she would be successful, but, uh…

357
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:45,366
What is it?

358
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:48,119
- Mine-san!
- Mom! Are you all right?

359
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:50,663
Mom?

360
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:53,082
I'm all right. Don't worry.

361
00:29:53,166 --> 00:29:56,252
I need to rest a little bit,
but I'm all right.

362
00:29:57,962 --> 00:29:58,963
Mom?

363
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:00,799
Mom?

364
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:02,717
Are you sure?

365
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:12,936
Huh? What's going on there?

366
00:30:26,616 --> 00:30:27,575
Here is good.

367
00:30:28,326 --> 00:30:29,744
Here you are, miss.

368
00:30:32,413 --> 00:30:34,332
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

369
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:37,460
- Hey!
- Come out, you coward!

370
00:30:37,544 --> 00:30:39,128
Pay us what we're owed!

371
00:30:39,212 --> 00:30:41,089
- Enough is enough!
- Come out here and pay!

372
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:42,882
- You thieving bastard!
- You gotta pay us!

373
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:44,175
Come out here right now!

374
00:30:44,259 --> 00:30:46,010
Excuse me. Pardon me.

375
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:48,221
- Enough is enough!
- Sorry. Excuse me.

376
00:30:48,304 --> 00:30:49,848
Just come out here and face us!

377
00:30:49,931 --> 00:30:50,890
- Hey!
- Come on!

378
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:53,518
Excuse me,
what exactly is everybody doing here?

379
00:30:54,102 --> 00:30:54,936
Hey.

380
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:57,605
- You the owner of this place?
- Yes.

381
00:30:58,314 --> 00:31:00,441
Pay me for the plumbing work right now!

382
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:02,527
- No! I was here first!
- No, you weren't! I was!

383
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:05,071
Just hold on a minute.
I still don't understand what's going on.

384
00:31:05,154 --> 00:31:07,949
- Are you trying to play dumb with us?
- No, I'm serious.

385
00:31:08,032 --> 00:31:09,117
What is all this about?

386
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:12,579
I did all of the electrical work here,
but I haven't gotten paid yet.

387
00:31:12,662 --> 00:31:13,830
Same goes for these guys.

388
00:31:13,913 --> 00:31:14,873
That's right!

389
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:16,082
Impossible.

390
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,459
Sudo was in charge of all that.

391
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:21,546
The only thing we got from Sudo
were these promissory notes.

392
00:31:21,629 --> 00:31:23,339
The due date is tomorrow!

393
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:25,800
At this rate, it's all gonna default!

394
00:31:26,301 --> 00:31:28,887
This is getting us nowhere.
Bring Sudo out here!

395
00:31:28,970 --> 00:31:31,264
- Yeah!
- I'm gonna check on it right away.

396
00:31:31,347 --> 00:31:34,058
Would you all mind leaving for today?

397
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:37,186
I have a wife and four kids to feed.
You think this is a joke?

398
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:39,063
You're wrong!

399
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:42,233
You won't get away with this!
Pay us what you owe us!

400
00:31:43,109 --> 00:31:44,402
What is going on?

401
00:31:44,485 --> 00:31:45,695
Where's Sudo-san?

402
00:31:45,778 --> 00:31:48,364
In Karuizawa.
I think he'll be back tomorrow.

403
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:50,575
Look, sis,
I… I just checked with the bank.

404
00:31:50,658 --> 00:31:52,535
Uh, our balance is zero.

405
00:31:52,619 --> 00:31:54,829
They said Sudo withdrew all of it.

406
00:31:55,997 --> 00:31:57,665
I can't believe he set us up!

407
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,709
He was a conman after all!

408
00:32:01,544 --> 00:32:03,129
What are we gonna do?

409
00:32:46,756 --> 00:32:48,549
IIJIMA DETECTIVE AGENCY

410
00:33:08,277 --> 00:33:14,575
TO: SUDO REAL ESTATE INC.
INVESTIGATION REPORT

411
00:33:20,832 --> 00:33:23,459
Honestly, I was just
a little nervous around you.

412
00:33:33,803 --> 00:33:35,930
CREATE A SENSE OF INTIMACY,
BE A WAR ORPHAN?

413
00:33:36,014 --> 00:33:38,808
I was… a war orphan.

414
00:33:45,606 --> 00:33:47,400
DROPOUT, INFERIORITY COMPLEX

415
00:33:47,483 --> 00:33:50,403
Actually, she's the owner
of three clubs in Ginza.

416
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:55,658
INEXPERIENCED IN LOVE, SEDUCE HER

417
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:01,706
ACT HONEST

418
00:34:01,789 --> 00:34:06,002
Then I'll definitely sever all ties
with my illicit business.

419
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:12,425
<i>Will you be my business partner</i>
<i>for this place?</i>

420
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:14,969
So I'll put up the remaining 100 million.

421
00:34:19,265 --> 00:34:20,224
SUBJECT: EIICHI NAKAZONO

422
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:23,394
What kind of person is Nakazono-san?

423
00:34:23,478 --> 00:34:24,937
MUST ELIMINATE

424
00:34:25,021 --> 00:34:29,067
I have to tell you,
I don't want you seeing him anymore.

425
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:16,114
<i>That was the day that my true hell began.</i>

426
00:35:26,499 --> 00:35:29,085
FOR SALE

427
00:35:44,267 --> 00:35:47,728
NOTICE OF CLOSURE

428
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:52,400
PROPERTY FOR SALE

429
00:36:04,453 --> 00:36:05,997
TEMPORARY CLOSURE

430
00:37:08,935 --> 00:37:09,894
Who's there?

431
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,653
Hisao.

432
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:30,081
Are those debt collectors still out there?

433
00:37:39,298 --> 00:37:40,174
What is it?

434
00:38:15,459 --> 00:38:16,419
Mom.

435
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:19,505
She collapsed at the restaurant.

436
00:38:20,006 --> 00:38:21,674
They said it was a heart attack.

437
00:38:26,470 --> 00:38:29,432
She was worried about you
right until the very end.

438
00:38:31,142 --> 00:38:32,560
A fortune teller

439
00:38:33,978 --> 00:38:35,479
told her that

440
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:39,108
soon you would be seeing hell.

441
00:38:43,362 --> 00:38:45,281
The debt collectors
were coming to our house!

442
00:38:45,364 --> 00:38:46,741
Did you know that?

443
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:50,745
But Mom just

444
00:38:52,038 --> 00:38:53,789
apologized to them

445
00:38:54,832 --> 00:38:57,418
and gave them all the money she had.

446
00:39:01,130 --> 00:39:03,716
You've always been so selfish.

447
00:39:05,593 --> 00:39:07,678
You're responsible for killing her.

448
00:39:20,024 --> 00:39:22,485
Don't come to the funeral or to the wake!

449
00:39:22,985 --> 00:39:26,280
I don't want debt collectors
following you there. Do you hear?

450
00:40:10,157 --> 00:40:11,742
Nakazono-san.

451
00:40:11,826 --> 00:40:13,202
My condolences.

452
00:41:39,079 --> 00:41:40,498
Takiguchi-san.

453
00:41:42,166 --> 00:41:44,126
Now, now. Don't be a fool.

454
00:41:47,922 --> 00:41:49,673
Please just let me die.

455
00:41:50,883 --> 00:41:53,093
I think you should put that thing down.

456
00:41:54,261 --> 00:41:55,179
There.

457
00:42:03,395 --> 00:42:05,981
I'm gonna take care of all of your debts.

458
00:42:10,069 --> 00:42:12,863
I'm gonna get the deed to this place back,

459
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:15,282
and then you'll reopen the club.

460
00:42:17,034 --> 00:42:20,829
Then that way, you can repay me
little by little with your earnings.

461
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,752
Thank you very much.

462
00:42:31,590 --> 00:42:33,676
Thank you so very much.

463
00:42:39,056 --> 00:42:42,226
But… there's one condition.

464
00:42:44,311 --> 00:42:45,771
From today onward,

465
00:42:46,605 --> 00:42:47,940
you'll be mine.

466
00:43:12,006 --> 00:43:13,632
<i>You did a very good job.</i>

467
00:43:14,174 --> 00:43:16,760
Took a bit longer
than I expected you to though.

468
00:43:17,553 --> 00:43:18,470
Well,

469
00:43:19,638 --> 00:43:21,890
I knew it wasn't gonna be so easy.

470
00:43:22,391 --> 00:43:25,311
She is the queen of Ginza, after all.

471
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,982
You picked a really good woman.

472
00:43:31,108 --> 00:43:34,153
From now on,
she's just a slave who serves her king.

473
00:43:35,321 --> 00:43:37,615
That woman has a knack for making money.

474
00:43:39,074 --> 00:43:41,160
A money tree and also

475
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:45,497
a mistress
that you can play with as you like.

476
00:43:46,206 --> 00:43:47,750
You got the best of both worlds.

477
00:43:47,833 --> 00:43:48,876
Right.

478
00:43:49,585 --> 00:43:53,589
I'll have my fun with her
and keep her in limbo.

479
00:43:57,509 --> 00:43:58,927
A slave, huh?

480
00:44:02,765 --> 00:44:04,266
My condolences.

481
00:44:26,413 --> 00:44:27,373
Stop!

482
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:29,041
Stay away from me! No!

483
00:44:30,125 --> 00:44:33,545
<i>Hell is like a bottomless swamp.</i>

484
00:44:33,629 --> 00:44:35,089
Get away!

485
00:44:36,215 --> 00:44:38,759
<i>The more you struggle,</i>
<i>the deeper you sink.</i>

486
00:44:38,842 --> 00:44:40,761
Stop it! No!

487
00:44:40,844 --> 00:44:42,513
<i>There's no way</i>
<i>to get out of it on your own.</i>

488
00:44:42,596 --> 00:44:43,514
Don't!

489
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:55,859
<i>All I could do was wait,</i>

490
00:44:57,444 --> 00:44:59,196
<i>hoping that someone</i>

491
00:45:00,239 --> 00:45:03,367
<i>would save me from this hell.</i>
